SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 113
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences on the passing of Martha
Elizabeth Odom.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere and heartfelt condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of
3 Louisiana upon the passing of Martha Elizabeth Odom.
4 WHEREAS, it is with sincere regret and immense sorrow that members of the Senate
5 of the Legislature of Louisiana have learned of the passing of Martha Elizabeth Odom, on
6 April 23, 2026, at the age of seventeen; and
7 WHEREAS, Martha was welcomed into this world on May 23, 2008, in Biloxi,
8 Mississippi, to her loving parents, Michael and Brooke Bingham Odom, and later made her
9 home in Lafayette, Louisiana, where she flourished into a multitalented, compassionate,
10 intelligent, inspiring, and remarkable young woman; and
11 WHEREAS, Martha was thoughtful, intentional, and lived each and every moment
12 with purpose; and
13 WHEREAS, she studied and trained in classical ballet her entire life, maturing into
14 a talented and beautiful ballerina, and shared her talents on stage in ten performances of the
15 Lafayette Ballet Theatre's production of The Nutcracker; and
16 WHEREAS, the Ballet Studio was a formative place where she found joy, strength,
17 and peace, and through her dance training, she developed a love for teaching young dancers
18 and gained the discipline and inner confidence to explore and embrace other art forms; and
