1 WHEREAS, throughout her high school career at Ascension Episcopal School,
2 Martha pursued theater, writing, and music with the same steadfast dedication she applied
3 to all her endeavors, appearing in five school musicals and three plays, earning recognition
4 in the Writes of Spring Regional Writing Contest for her undeniable gift as a storyteller, and
5 receiving multiple short fiction awards for three consecutive years; and
6 WHEREAS, in addition to her artistic accomplishments, Martha was a standout
7 softball player, playing on the junior varsity and varsity teams and earning freshman all-
8 district honorable mention; she was a leader on the varsity soccer team for four years, being
9 voted the happiest team player and team captain during her senior season; and during her
10 senior year she was selected for the varsity tennis team; and
11 WHEREAS, to further broaden her horizons, Martha was an active member in
12 several school clubs including the Creative Writing Club, Robotics Club, Beta Club, Mu
13 Alpha Theta, National English Honor Society, and Rho Kappa National Social Studies
14 Honor Society; and
15 WHEREAS, through her experiences, Martha emerged into a strong, thoughtful,
16 natural leader; she was selected to attend Louisiana Girls State and she served as Editor-in-
17 Chief of The Authored Ascension, her school's paper, as an Ascension Ambassador, and as
18 the communications officer for Rho Kappa National Social Studies Honor Society; and
19 WHEREAS, Martha's presence and abilities were noticed by many with school
20 counselors recounting how "Martha is undaunted by challenges, and even with her quiet
21 nature, she does not shy away from approaching a microphone, stepping into the spotlight,
22 or speaking her mind"; and
23 WHEREAS, in her free time, Martha could often be found curled up with a book and
24 a matcha beverage, or playing cards and board games with friends; she cherished car rides
25 with her sister, listening to their favorite songs on the way to school, and she was honored
26 to be presented at the Krewe of Gabriel 2025 Fall Ball, where she was escorted by and
27 danced the night away with her father; and
28 WHEREAS, upon graduation, Martha was accepted to attend the University of the
29 South in Sewanee, Tennessee, as a member of the class of 2030, where she planned to major
30 in English and Creative Writing and Rhetoric, and minor in Dance; and
