1 WHEREAS, Martha was preceded in death by her paternal grandparents, Dr. James
2 C. and Martha Tolley Davis Odom and her uncle, James Calhoun "Cal" Odom, Jr.; and
3 WHEREAS, Martha leaves behind family and friends who will cherish her memory,
4 including her parents; her sister, Margaret Odom; maternal grandparents, Kenneth and Joan
5 Bingham; godmother, Allison Clarke; her aunts and uncles, Brent and Gina Bingham,
6 Suzanne Odom, Cade and Dave Cheshire, Catherine and Tom Pankey; and a host of cousins
7 who loved and adored her; and
8 WHEREAS, Martha Elizabeth Odom was a light to everyone around her and
9 recognized and nurtured that same light in others; she carried herself with quiet strength and
10 grace and will be remembered by all those who knew her for her unwavering compassion,
11 wit, wisdom, sense of humor, and her breathtaking smile.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
13 does hereby honor the life of Martha Elizabeth Odom and her numerous accomplishments
14 during her short life and does hereby express the sincere and heartfelt condolences to the
15 family of Martha Elizabeth Odom.
16 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
17 Martha's parents, Michael and Brooke Bingham Odom.
